claim.claim-text:
A power conversion apparatus to be applied to a generation system that interconnects with an alternating current power system, the power conversion apparatus characterized by comprising:
an inverter circuit that converts a direct current power into an alternating current power;
system voltage measurement means for measuring a system voltage of the alternating current power system;
voltage drop detection means for detecting a voltage drop of the alternating current power system, based on the system voltage measured by the system voltage measurement means;
direct current power measurement means for measuring a direct current power to be input into the inverter circuit;
alternating current command value calculation means for calculating an alternating current command value to control an alternating current output from the inverter circuit, based on the direct current power measured by the direct current power measurement means and the system voltage measured by the system voltage measurement means; and
current limiting means for decreasing a current limit value to limit the alternating current command value calculated by the alternating current command value calculation means, when the voltage drop is detected by the voltage drop detection means.

A control apparatus for a power conversion apparatus that controls the power conversion apparatus to be applied to a generation system which interconnects with an alternating current power system and containing an inverter circuit which converts a direct current power into an alternating current power, the control apparatus characterized by comprising:
system voltage measurement means for measuring a system voltage of the alternating current power system;
voltage drop detection means for detecting a voltage drop of the alternating current power system, based on the system voltage measured by the system voltage measurement means;
direct current power measurement means for measuring a direct current power to be input into the inverter circuit;
alternating current command value calculation means for calculating an alternating current command value to control an alternating current output from the inverter circuit, based on the direct current power measured by the direct current power measurement means and the system voltage measured by the system voltage measurement means; and
current limiting means for decreasing a current limit value to limit the alternating current command value calculated by the alternating current command value calculation means, when the voltage drop is detected by the voltage drop detection means.

A control method for a power conversion apparatus that controls the power conversion apparatus to be applied to a generation system which interconnects with an alternating current power system and containing an inverter circuit which converts a direct current power into an alternating current power, the control method characterized by comprising:
measuring a system voltage of the alternating current power system;
detecting a voltage drop of the alternating current power system, based on the measured system voltage;
calculating an alternating current command value to control an alternating current output from the inverter circuit, based on a power of the direct current power input into the inverter circuit and the measured system voltage; and
decreasing a current limit value to limit the calculated alternating current command value, when the voltage drop of the alternating current power system is detected.
